        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7826.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from T. H. Farrer, 19 June 1871</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <hi rend="italic">Ophrys apifera</hi>, the bee orchid. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7826.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from T. H. Farrer, 19 June 1871</ref> and n. 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7826.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from T. H. Farrer, 19 June 1871</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD was in London from 24 to 30 June 1871 (see CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">No record of a visit by Farrer to Down has been found. CD spent most of August 1871 at Haredene in Albury, Surrey.</note>
        </div>        
            
